In this article, President Biden delivers a speech in Israel, expressing solidarity with the country in the wake of a recent terrorist attack by Hamas. He condemns the atrocities committed by the terrorist group and promises to work towards the release of hostages and the safe return of all those affected. President Biden emphasizes the importance of Israel's safety and pledges to provide support for its defense. He announces a $100 million funding for humanitarian assistance in Gaza and the West Bank. He acknowledges the suffering of both Israelis and Palestinians and calls for the protection of civilian lives. President Biden urges Israel to uphold its values of democracy and the rule of law, and emphasizes the need for peace and a two-state solution. He concludes by assuring Israel that the United States stands with them and will continue to support them.